0in%20an%20organized%20criminal%20network%20to%20obtain%20fuel%20in%20violation%20of%20international%20sanctions.%20The%20network%20relies%20on%20a%20complex%20and%20convoluted%20shipping%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20center%20of%20this%20operation%20is%20the%20tanker%20%26quot%3BDiamond%208.%26quot%3B%20Satellite%20imagery%20shows%20how%20fuel%20is%20transferred%20from%20one%20ship%20to%20another%2C%20eventually%20arriving%20in%20North%20Korean%20ports.%20This%20secretive%20supply%20chain%20allows%20North%20Korea%20to%20bypass%20international%20sanctions%20and%20continue%20developing%20its%20weapons%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20constant%20game%20of%20cat%20and%20mouse%20and%20they%20are%20always%20trying%20to%20stay%20ahead.%20You%20cannot%20see%20what%20they%20are%20doing%20without%20satellite%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20Lauren%20Sung%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20The%20Center%20for%20Advanced%20Defense%20Studies%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noindex%2Cnofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcjr4pr0gyyzo%5C%22%3EBBC%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20is%20estimated%20that%20Russia%20has%20been%20supplying%20more%20than%20a%20million%20barrels%20of%20oil%20to%20North%20Korea%2C%20as%20a%20payment%20for%20the%20troops%20they%20have%20received%20from%20them%20for%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorth%20Korea%20is%20the%20only%20country%20that%20cannot%20buy%20oil%20on%20the%20open%20market%20and%20the%20number%20of%20barrels%20it%20can%20receive%20is%20capped%20at%20500%2C000%20by%20the%20UN.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20against%20UN%20sanctions%20to%20transfer%20or%20sell%20oil%20to%20North%20Korea%20except%20in%20small%20quantities%2C%20in%20order%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20do%20not%20develop%20nuclear%20weapons%20and%20the%20satellite%20images%20clearly%20show%20violation%20of%20the%20sanctions.%20Moreover%2C%20there%20are%20pictures%20to%20support%20the%20same%2C%20where%20it%20is%20visible%20that%20the%20tankers%20arrive%20empty%20and%20leave%20full.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20is%20providing%20Vladimir%20Putin%20with%20a%20lifeline%20to%20continue%20his%20war%2C%20Russia%20is%20quietly%20providing%20North%20Korea%20with%20a%20lifeline%20of%20its%20own%2C%26quot%3B%20Joe%20Byrne%20from%20the%20Open%20Source%20Centre%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUK%20Foreign%20Secretary%20David%20Lammy%20has%20told%20the%20BBC%20that%2C%20%26quot%3BTo%20keep%20fighting%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20Russia%20has%20become%20increasingly%20reliant%20on%20North%20Korea%20for%20troops%20and%20weapons%20in%20exchange%20for%20oil.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20March%2C%20North%20Korea%20has%20received%20more%20oil%20from%20Russia%20than%20double%20the%20annual%20cap.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Go%20Myong-hyun%2C%20a%20senior%20research%20fellow%20at%20South%20Korea's%20Institute%20for%20National%20Security%20Strategy%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20sending%20your%20people%20to%20die%20in%20a%20foreign%20war%2C%20a%20million%20barrels%20of%20oil%20is%20just%20not%20sufficient%20reward.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShin%20Won-sik%2C%20Seoul's%20top%20security%20advisor%2C%20has%20said%20that%20Russia%20seems%20to%20have%20helped%20North%20Korea%20with%20financial%20and%20technological%20support%20for%20its%20space%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20real%20concern%20is%20what%20else%20can%20be%20traded%20between%20the%20two%20countries%2C%20since%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20has%20stepped%20up%20his%20support%20for%20Russia's%20war.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1732300320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fr8d53hbg_vladimir-putin-kim-jong-un-reuters_625x300_22_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsatellite-imagery-exposes-russia-smuggling-illicit-oil-to-north-korea-7082733%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Despite%20international%20efforts%20to%20sanction%20North%20Korea%20for%20developing%20weapons%20of%20mass%20destruction%2C%20the%20country%20continues%20to%20receive%20illicit%20supplies%20of%20refined%20petroleum%20products.%20These%20products%20are%20crucial%20for%20manufacturing%20weapons.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsatellite-imagery-exposes-russia-smuggling-illicit-oil-to-north-korea-7082733%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Centre%20Plans%20To%20Examine%20Burnt%20Area%20After%20Farmers%20Timing%20Crop%20Fires%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ECentre%20plans%20to%20clamp%20down%20on%20polluting%20farm%20fires%20by%20measuring%20the%20areas%20burnt%20instead%20of%20live%20blazes%2C%20after%20reports%20that%20farmers%20were%20burning%20paddy%20waste%20or%20stubble%20at%20times%20when%20satellites%20were%20not%20passing%20overhead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20currently%20uses%20data%20from%20NASA%20satellites%20that%20pass%20twice%20a%20day%20over%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20to%20monitor%20farm%20fires%2C%20which%20are%20a%20major%20contributor%20to%20the%20smog%20that%20envelopes%20the%20national%20capital%20region%20(NCR)%20each%20winter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Commission%20for%20Air%20Quality%20Management%2C%20a%20government%20body%20responsible%20for%20air%20quality%20in%20the%20NCR%2C%20said%20on%20Friday%20that%20India's%20space%20agency%20had%20been%20asked%20in%20January%20to%20develop%20a%20system%20to%20study%20burnt%20areas%20to%20count%20farm%20fires.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20protocol%20has%20actually%20been%20developed%20and%20is%20currently%20being%20tested%2C%26quot%3B%20Additional%20Solicitor%20General%20Aishwarya%20Bhati%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20after%20an%20adviser%20to%20the%20court%20said%20on%20Monday%20that%20the%20current%20system%20counted%20fires%20over%20a%20limited%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20experts%20suspect%20that%20farmers%20have%2C%20over%20time%2C%20become%20aware%20of%20the%20surveillance%20period%20and%20shifted%20the%20time%20of%20burning%20their%20crop%20waste%20to%20evade%20the%20NASA%20satellites%2C%20because%20of%20which%20while%20counts%20were%20lower%20this%20year%2C%20pollution%20levels%20were%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20said%20on%20Friday%20that%20data%20from%20stationary%20satellites%20was%20%26quot%3Bsub-optimal%26quot%3B%20and%20not%20%26quot%3Bactionable%26quot%3B%2C%20dismissing%20an%20earlier%20direction%20from%20the%20court%20to%20use%20them%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi%20has%20been%20battling%20hazardous%20air%20this%20month%2C%20with%20the%20air%20quality%20index%20(AQI)%20touching%20a%20peak%20of%20494%20on%20a%20scale%20of%20500%20on%20Monday%2C%20when%20farm%20fires%20also%20recorded%20a%20high%20of%202%2C893%2C%20prompting%20the%20government%20to%20restrict%20vehicle%20movement%20and%20construction%20and%20shift%20schools%20to%20online%20teaching.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20considers%20an%20AQI%20of%200-50%20'good'%2C%20and%20above%20400%20'severe'%2C%20which%20poses%20a%20risk%20to%20healthy%20people%20and%20%26quot%3Bseriously%20impacts%26quot%3B%20those%20with%20existing%20diseases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi%20recorded%20a%20'very%20poor'%20AQI%20of%20374%20on%20Friday%2C%20authorities%20said%2C%20and%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Earth%20Sciences%20forecast%20it%20would%20remain%20in%20the%20same%20category%20(300-400)%20through%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20countries%20in%20South%20Asia%20also%20battle%20toxic%20air%20every%20year%20as%20cold%20air%20traps%20dust%2C%20smoke%2C%20and%20emissions%2C%20and%20some%20studies%20say%20rising%20air%20pollution%20can%20cut%20a%20person's%20life%20expectancy%20in%20the%20region%20by%20more%20than%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%2